gomodel:SYNGO_3023  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Kv2.1-IR is restricted to the postsynaptic membrane and is clustered at specific synaptic sites on the membrane\"\n- \"Most importantly, the labelling was always concentrated at the postsynaptic side of the synaptic apposition, with very little migration of reaction product into the synaptic cleft (Fig. 5). The immunolabelling is concentrated close to the surface membrane, and appears closely associated with the subsynaptic cistern (Fig. 5A, B and C). \". Experimental description: - \"Adult male Sprague-Dawley rats were killed...\"" ;
